Abuja – The All Progressives Congress (APC) has revised timetable and schedule of activities for its presidential, governorship, senate, national, and state assemblies’ primaries. Felix Morka, National Publicity Secretary of the ruling party, disclosed this on Wednesday after the weekly meeting of the party’s National Working Committee (NWC), stating that the adjustment was final. Accordingly, he said the governorship and House of Representatives primaries will hold on Thursday, May 26, 2022, while the primaries for Senate and state Assembly primaries will come up Friday, May 27, 2022. -Advertisement- Morka said the Appeals for governorship and House of Representatives primaries will hold same day, Friday, May 27, while the Appeals for Senate and House of Assembly comes up Saturday, May 28. The NWC, he said, has slightly adjusted the party’s special convention and presidential primaries to now hold Sunday, May 29, through Monday, May 30, 2022. On the rumoured zoning of the presidential and vice presidential tickets to North- East and South-East geopolitical zones, respectively, Morka said no such decision was taken by the NWC. He added that whenever the party takes such far reaching decision, it will be made public. He equally denied the rumoured return of the APC presidential form by former President Goodluck Jonathan, stating categorically that he was not aware of it. POLL The national secretariat of the APC earlier in the day went abuzz when report filtered in that some faceless persons returned the form for the former president.